questionText:
Voici un extrait de code Express :
```javascript
app.use(session({
  secret: 'monSecretSuperLong',
  resave: false,
  saveUninitialized: false,
  cookie: { httpOnly: true }
}));

app.post('/login', (req, res) => {
  const { username } = req.body;
  req.session.user = username;
  res.send('Connecté');
});

app.get('/profile', (req, res) => {
  if (req.session.user) {
    res.send(`Bienvenue ${req.session.user}`);
  } else {
    res.status(401).send('Non authentifié');
  }
});
```
Que renvoie la route `/profile` après un `/login` réussi ?
